{
  "texts": [
    "Lin et al. [45] address the challenges of teaching AI in schools, presenting effective instructional design components based on experienced teachers' perspectives, including obstacles to teaching AI, interactive design thinking processes, and orienteering AI knowledge for social good.",
    "Chai et al. [14] shift the focus to students, examining their perceptions of learning AI.",
    "Their research model integrates the theory of planned behavior and self-determination theory, revealing the interrelationships among factors like AI knowledge, programming efficacy, autonomy, AI for social good, and learning resources.",
    "The findings offer insights into designing AI curricula that consider students' needs and satisfaction.",
    "Hsu et al. [34] contribute by evaluating the learning effectiveness of the MIT App Inventor platform and its Personal Image Classifier tool in an interdisciplinary AI-STEAM course."
  ]
}